What Makes It Industry Relevant
It is not hardcoded to any one truck variant. Adding a new configuration requires no code change — just ODE data to train a PINN if desired, and a registry entry. The ODE path means it always works even before any PINN is trained. The verification step means engineers get a physically confirmed result, not just a surrogate’s word for it. And the architecture naturally extends to configurable objective functions beyond cabin RMS, parallel scenario comparison runs, and eventually DFMEA and RAG integration — without redesigning the core.

The Honest Build Order
First get the full pipeline working ODE-only end to end in LangGraph. Then validate your PINN for 6x2 NRS laden and slot it in as the fast path. Then expand configs. That way something works completely on day one and the system improves incrementally.

